      java.lang.Double DawidSkene.getWorkerCost(Worker w, int method)
      Estimates the cost for worker using various methods: COST_NAIVE: We do not adjust the label assigned by the worker (i.e., use the "hard" label) COST_ADJUSTED: We use the error rates of the worker and compute the posterior probability vector for each object COST_MINIMIZED: Like COST_ADJUSTED but we also assign the object to the category that generates the minimum expected error
